    bibo:volume "5178" ;
    dc:creator "Delvare, Gérard; Shaw, Mark R." ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Characterisation of some species groups of Brachymeria (Hymenoptera: Chalcididae), with a review of the B. tibialis-group and description of a new species parasitizing Zygaena pupae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033993>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033987>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033984>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033991> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033993>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12A-E. Labelling of the primary types of Brachymeria tibialis and its synonyms. A, lectotype of Chalcis tibialis. B. Lectotype of Chalcis distinguenda. C. Lectotype of Chalcis scirropoda. D. Type of Chalcis boops. E. Lectotype of Chalcis quettaensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7033993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033987>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9A–F. Comparative characters of B. tibialis and B. zygaenae. 9A–C, B. tibialis, ♂. 9D–F, Brachymeria zygaenae, paratype ♂. 8A and 8D, antennal flagellum with base enlarged; 8B and 8E, hind leg with sculpture of metafemur enlarged; 8C and 8F, apex of metatibia and hind tarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7033987/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033984>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8A–H. Comparative characters of B. tibialis and B. zygaenae. 8A–D, B. tibialis, ♀. 8E–H, Brachymeria zygaenae, holotype ♀. 8A and 8E, mesopleuron in lateral view with adscrobal area enlarged; 8B and 8F, hind leg with sculpture of metafemur enlarged; 8C and 8G, apex of metatibia and hind tarsus; 8D and 8H, hind pretarsus. Abbreviation: fc, falcate seta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7033984/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7033991>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11A–D. Phenotypes of Brachymeria tibialis. 11A–C, B. tibialis ♀ from Morocco, Moyen Atlas, phenotype rufofemorata. 11D, B. tibialis ♀ from Iran, phenotype turkestanica. 11A, habitus in dorsal view; 11B, metasoma in lateral view; 10C and 10D, hind leg." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7033991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

